## Proposed changes

optimize bitmap function count, use roaring cardinality method, this will more fast than current version,
for a simple benchmark 
```
#include <benchmark/benchmark.h>
#include <roaring/roaring.hh>
const int maxn=40960;
static roaring::Roaring r1;
static roaring::Roaring r2;
void init()
{
  for (int i = 0; i < maxn; ++i) {
    r1.add(rand());
    r2.add(rand());
  }
}

static void and_cardinality(benchmark::State& state) {
  long card =0;
  for (auto _ : state){
      card = r1.and_cardinality(r2);
  }
  std::string str=std::to_string(card);
}

static void cardinality_after_and(benchmark::State& state) {
  long card =0;
  for (auto _ : state){
      card = (r1&r2).cardinality();
  }
  std::string str=std::to_string(card);
}

BENCHMARK(and_cardinality)->Iterations(1000);
BENCHMARK(cardinality_after_and)->Iterations(1000);
// Run the benchmark
int main(int argc, char** argv)
{
   init();
   ::benchmark::Initialize(&argc, argv);
   ::benchmark::RunSpecifiedBenchmarks();
}
```
 
use `and_cardinality` is  about 3 to 4 times faster than first `and` the cal `cardinality`
```
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Benchmark                                      Time             CPU   Iterations
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
and_cardinality/iterations:1000           796634 ns       794637 ns         1000
cardinality_after_and/iterations:1000    2926119 ns      2919778 ns         1000
```

